      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "In my case &quot;This configuration does not contain a load balancer.&quot; so PORT variable in &quot;Environment properties&quot; sorted the problem."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1008417,
      "reputation" : 961,
      "user_id" : 1021522,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/KKrxL.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Sujit Kamthe",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1021522/sujit-kamthe"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 32,
    "last_activity_date" : 1609338384,
    "last_edit_date" : 1609338384,
    "creation_date" : 1609157214,
    "answer_id" : 65477363,
    "question_id" : 54612962,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This happens because the application load balancer by default points to the <strong>Port 80</strong> of the nginx server in EC2 instance. The nginx is configured to forward requests to <strong>Port 5000</strong> by default, whereas out application server runs on <strong>Port 8080</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Default Nginx Configuration</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/CGqyn.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/CGqyn.png\" alt=\"Default Nginx Configuration\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Expected Nginx Configuration</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/s4HIJ.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/s4HIJ.png\" alt=\"Expected Nginx Configuration\" /></a></p>\n<ol>\n<li>This can be fixed using an environment property named <code>PORT</code> and pointing it to 8080\nGo to configuration &gt; Environment Properties and add the property\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/KxH2j.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/KxH2j.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Refer AWS Document: <a href=\"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticbeanstalk/latest/dg/java-se-nginx.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticbeanstalk/latest/dg/java-se-nginx.html</a></p>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li><p>Another option to fix this is to point application load balancer to the application server port(8080) directly instead of the nginx(80.\nYou can configure 8080 as the process port.\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/R3XEY.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/R3XEY.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Another way to fix this would be to set port to 5000 in the spring boot application by using server.port property.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
